description: Archie's car has been a staple of Archie Comics since the beginning -- and it's been a lemon for just as long! Even back in the Roarin' 40's, Archie's jalopy was in a constant state of disrepair, much to the chagrin of his friends! While it may not be reliable, it sure creates some hilarious situations for Archie! Join us as we present over 100 pages of car capers as only the Archie art team can tell. This book is a digital exclusive, too-perfect for long car trips!

This is no game anymore. Someone is trying to kill PJ, but is it an overzealous combatant in the arena competition or another? Or possibly, someone looking to settle a score with the man behind the man - Benoist? Meanwhile, Malikai confronts the strange messiah who has entranced the believers of Gabriel's Voice, but are his actions justified or just plain jealous?

Join veteran Soulfire scribe JT Krul, along with the amazing artistic talents of V. Ken Marion and Kyle Ritter, as an all-new direction for Michael Turner's fantasy epic Soulfire continues!

deck:
Eric Hoffman led a life of privilege.  As the only son of a multi-billionaire weapons contractor, the sixteen-year-old's world was rocked with the death of his father.  And then the discovery that his dad was still alive -- and secretly the ABYSS -- the world's greatest super-villain.

To stop a plot to destroy San Francisco, Eric takes up his father's mantle.  But will the real heroes accept good in evil clothing?
